KW  - Foreign Exchange
KW  - Intervention
KW  - Information
KW  - Sharing
KW  - Exchange Rates
AB  - This paper develops a model of information sharing among heterogeneously informed agents and it uses the model to examine a rationale for intervention in the foreign exchange market. The model shows that in a partially revealing rational expectations equilibrium, some agents can gain by sharing among themselves private information about transitory exchange rate disturbances. In this setting, a central bank can affect the exchange rate by aggregating and disseminating agents’ information. The paper also illustrates the usefulness of intervention as a way to transmit that information.
ER  - 

